[Get Started](https://mystnodes.com/onboarding)

Earnings are based on your region, the amount of bandwidth and time you can contribute to the network. The more users who connect to your stable node, the higher your earning potential.

[data:image/png;base64,](data:image/png;base64,)

More than 20,000 people are using our apps everyday and we are happy to help them and make their lives better.

Why should you become a Mysterium node operator? Open-up the web for the ones behind (electronic) walls and earn money while doing so. Setup a node within half an hour. There really is no better way to spend the next 30 minutes of your life...

After looking into "how to help the dvpn community and get rewarded in cryptocurrency" i came across the Mysterium Network. It immediately caught my attention, as this is exactly what I was looking for. Setting up a node was super simple as multiple platforms are supported out of the box. When I ran into an issue about port forwarding, the mysterium community was right there to assist and solve the issue in no time. The node is running ever since and while other users are using my internet connection to freely browse without censorship, i make some crypto on the side :)

At the beginning I was indecisive about becoming a node-runner and also a bit skeptical about the project itself, mainly because I was quite rusty in my technical skills and the available documentation about the project at that time was not very clear for me. Very soon I realised that only minimal technical understanding (not even skills) is needed to run a node and with the help of the community of node-runners and the Mysterium team that are very supportive, running a node became like a hobby, really enjoyable and effortless. As time went by, I started to understand more and more the technological part (I even become a beta-tester myself) but most importantly I started to understand the project itself and its potential, and how it can really help to boost freedom and fight against censorship, without forgetting the passive income that represents being a node-runner, just sharing your bandwidth to get a sweet profit. Now I manage six residential nodes (of friends and family) in two different countries, and looking forward to increasing that number.

Mysterium is creating a decentralised virtual private network (VPN) and with this it is providing a free internet for everyone. You may already know that internet providers can access all browsing history and this makes it possible for governments to ban or even punish citizens when they have written things that the government does not agree with. To provide this service anyone can run a Mysterium Node from home that adds VPN services to the network. Node runners are rewarded for providing their hardware for this cause. Because I believe in freedom of internet use for the whole world I am running a few nodes. I get rewarded for doing this (MYST tokens are earned for running a node) but the rewards (at this moment) are not comparable to all the work I have done to install and manage those nodes. I want to help the Mysterium team so this great service gets known to the world and so that everyone will use the Mysterium VPN service.

I believe in a less restrictive internet where governments or ISPs are not the withholding of information. This seems to be even more important in current times where citizens risk being forcibly detained because they are trying to spread information to the rest of the world but are being tracked online by their government.
